# AI Dungeon Master — Caddy reverse proxy (spec §14.3)
#
# Replace the placeholder domain with your own (point its DNS A/AAAA record at
# the NAS, e.g. via deSEC). Caddy obtains and renews TLS certs automatically.

dnd.example.org {
	reverse_proxy app:3000
}

# ALTERNATIVE — Tailscale (spec §14.3):
# Skip Caddy and public exposure entirely. Run the app on your tailnet and
# reach it over Tailscale (or Tailscale Serve for HTTPS on a *.ts.net name).
# In that setup, drop the caddy service from docker-compose.yml and publish
# the app's port on the tailnet instead.
